==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unruly
<hw>Un*rul"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Unrulier</adjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Unruliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>rule</ets>. Cf. <er>Ruly</er>.]</ety> <def>Not
submissive to rule; disregarding restraint; disposed to violate;
turbulent; ungovernable; refractory; <as>as, an <ex>unruly</ex> boy;
<ex>unruly</ex> boy; <ex>unruly</ex> conduct.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But the tongue can no man tame; it is an <qex>unruly</qex> evil,
full of deadly poison.</q> <rj><qau>James iii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unrumple</ent>⟦br⟧
